frameDefinitions: An Agent (or inanimate Cause) affects a Set so that the number of entities that make up the Set changes from an Initial_number to a Final_number.
The action of an Agent or the occurrence of a Cause event returns an Entity to an earlier  state of vigor and strength.
A Protester (or Protesters) expresses a strong opinion either in support of or against an Issue, or the Action(s) of a Side which relate to the Issue.
The Creator creates a new entity, the Created_entity, possibly out of Components.
A group of Colonists from a Homeland migrate to and proceed to settle in a New_area.
These are words relating to filling containers and covering areas with some thing, things or substance, the Theme.
frameExamples: More and more resources have been devoted to halting rogue nation's <t>proliferation</t> of controlled nuclear technology.
Falling prices and wireless connectivity have <t>breathed new life</t> into the PDA market.
Several hundred Tibetans, already worried by inflation, took to the streets to <t>protest</t> at the new measures.
The Libyans were <t>generating</t> arms for export.
In the 7th century BC, Phoenicians <t>colonized</t> the eastern section of Libya.
Lionel Hutz <t>coated</t> the wall with paint.
listRoleDefinitions: The person who causes the <fen>Set</fen> to increase in number.
The scale along which the <fen>Set</fen> ranges in, i.e., number.
The entity whose amount is being changed.
The force that causes the change.
When the proliferating occurs.
The location where the <fen>Agent</fen> changes the number of the <fen>Set</fen>.
The concrete or abstract thing that is brought into an earlier state in which it was more effective and powerful.
The <fen>Agent</fen> puts the <fen>Entity</fen> into a state of renewed vigor.
An event or state whose occurrence brings about the <fen>Entity</fen>'s return to a vigorous state.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Agent</fen> causes the renewal of the <fen>Entity</fen>.
This role identifies the place where the Agent brings about the change in the <fen>Entity</fen>'s state.
The individual (or individuals) who holds an opinion on an Issue or Side.
The matter, usually concerning a course of action, which the <fen>Protester</fen> has an positive or negative opinion about.
The party or individual (generally associated with a particular position on an <fen>Issue</fen>) that the <fen>Protester</fen> sides with.
An action taken by a Side or a view that the Side takes on an issue which the <fen>Protester</fen> either supports or opposes.
The time period during which the Protesters express their opinions.
The location where the <fen>Protester</fen> takes <fen>Side</fen>s on an <fen>Issue</fen> .
The Creator creates a created entity.
This role identifies the entity that the Agent intentionally creates.
This role identifes the Time when an Agent intentionally creates a new entity.
This role identifies the place ehere the Agent intentionally creates the new entity.
A group of people who move together to an area outside their <fen>Homeland</fen> for the purpose of settling.
The <fen>Homeland</fen> is where the <fen>Colonists</fen> are originally from.
The <fen>Colonists</fen> move to the <fen>New_area</fen>, inhabiting it and (in the case of nation-states) extending the control of the <fen>Homeland</fen>.
The time at which the colonizing takes place.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the actor who instigates the filling.
The <fen>Theme</fen> is the physical object or substance which changes location.
The <fen>Goal</fen> is the area or container being filled. Goal is generally the NP Object in this frame.
An event which brings about the filling of the <fen>Goal</fen>.
When the filling occurs.
Where the filling takes place.
